{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/technical/medium/2021-08-22_How-to-build-Responsive-React-Native-Components-using-Restyle-7eb2742538a5/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Yajana Rao"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"ea53967f-1959-5a87-9888-c10c54d1a903","excerpt":"In this blog I will show you how to build a responsive react native components using Restyle.  The Restyle library provides a type-enforced system for building…","html":"<p>In this blog I will show you how to build a responsive react native components using Restyle.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7b008318c1022b3efd4bd0960ca15018/5a190/1__CSjAyYK8cK0T2amo2gCyQQ.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.08108108108109%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1  CSjAyYK8cK0T2amo2gCyQQ\"\n        title=\"1  CSjAyYK8cK0T2amo2gCyQQ\"\n        src=\"/static/7b008318c1022b3efd4bd0960ca15018/fcda8/1__CSjAyYK8cK0T2amo2gCyQQ.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7b008318c1022b3efd4bd0960ca15018/12f09/1__CSjAyYK8cK0T2amo2gCyQQ.png 148w,\n/static/7b008318c1022b3efd4bd0960ca15018/e4a3f/1__CSjAyYK8cK0T2amo2gCyQQ.png 295w,\n/static/7b008318c1022b3efd4bd0960ca15018/fcda8/1__CSjAyYK8cK0T2amo2gCyQQ.png 590w,\n/static/7b008318c1022b3efd4bd0960ca15018/5a190/1__CSjAyYK8cK0T2amo2gCyQQ.png 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The Restyle library provides a type-enforced system for building UI components in React Native with TypeScript. It’s a library for building UI libraries, with themability as the core focus.</p>\n<h4>Installation</h4>\n<p>Yarn</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">$ <span class=\"token function\">yarn</span> <span class=\"token function\">add</span> @shopify/restyle</code></pre></div>\n<p>NPM</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">$ <span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> @shopify/restyle</code></pre></div>\n<h4>Define Theme</h4>\n<p>Let’s create a global theme object. It should contain values for spacing, colors, breakpoints and more.</p>\n<p>Below is an example of how a basic theme could look.</p>\n<h4>Access theme</h4>\n<p>This theme should be passed to a <code class=\"language-text\">ThemeProvider</code> at the top of your React component tree:</p>\n<p>Here <code class=\"language-text\">Box</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">Text</code> are <a href=\"http://Breakpoints%20are%20defined%20as%20minimum%20widths%20%28inclusive%29%20for%20different%20target%20screen%20sizes%20where%20we%20want%20to%20apply%20differing%20styles.%20Consider%20giving%20your%20breakpoints%20names%20that%20give%20a%20general%20idea%20of%20the%20type%20of%20device%20the%20user%20is%20using.%20Breakpoints%20can%20be%20defined%20by%20either%20a%20single%20value%20%28width%29%20or%20an%20object%20containing%20both%20width%20and%20height:\"><em>predefined components</em></a> from <code class=\"language-text\">restyle</code></p>\n<h4>Creating responsive components</h4>\n<p>Using <a href=\"http://Breakpoints%20are%20defined%20as%20minimum%20widths%20%28inclusive%29%20for%20different%20target%20screen%20sizes%20where%20we%20want%20to%20apply%20differing%20styles.%20Consider%20giving%20your%20breakpoints%20names%20that%20give%20a%20general%20idea%20of%20the%20type%20of%20device%20the%20user%20is%20using.%20Breakpoints%20can%20be%20defined%20by%20either%20a%20single%20value%20%28width%29%20or%20an%20object%20containing%20both%20width%20and%20height:\"><em>breakpoints</em></a> we can specify different styles for different screen sizes.</p>\n<p>Let’s create a card example with acts as list on wide screen devices.</p>\n<p>Define the different values of flex direction for different screen sizes.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">flexDirection<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> phone<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> ‘column’<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> tablet<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> ‘row’ <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>For more details visit <a href=\"https://github.com/Shopify/restyle#breakpoints\"><em>restyle documentation</em></a></p>\n<h4>Reference:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://snack.expo.dev/@yajana/restyle\">Demo Snack</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://snack.expo.dev/@yajana/restyle\">ReStyle</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to build Responsive React Native Components using Restyle","date":"August 22, 2021","description":"In this blog I will show you how to build a responsive react native components using Restyle."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/technical/medium/2021-08-22_How-to-build-Responsive-React-Native-Components-using-Restyle-7eb2742538a5/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/technical/medium/2021-08-15_How-to-Debug-Redux-in-React-Native-using-Flipper-d785b46cf7bf/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How to Debug Redux in React Native using Flipper"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/technical/2021-08-23-dbms/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Database Management System"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["1105976633","1205699325","1246554614","2841359383","3336116537"]}